    "updated_at": "2016-01-12T07:12:00Z",
    "body": "Hm, Slack isn't installed in Program Files and it's still in this list as of Win10 11082. We do set the app model ID in the shortcut though - Squirrel.Windows will do this Automatically for you, it will set your AppUserModelID to `com.squirrel.PKGNAME.EXENAME` (so Atom's would be `com.squirrel.atom.atom`)\n\nNote that _just_ adding a shortcut is not enough, you need to call a special Shell method to set the App User Model ID in that shortcut: https://github.com/Squirrel/Squirrel.Windows/blob/1ed86dbc6f4cf3adb7d111986b28203c5178a27e/src/Squirrel/ShellFile.cs#L864\n"
